Preheat your oven to 200°C. Trim the @aubergine{1} and @courgette{1} then slice both into rounds 1cm thick. Halve the @bell pepper{1/2} and discard the core and seeds. Slice into 1cm wide strips. Halve, peel and thinly slice the @red onion{1}. Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1} (or use a #garlic press{}). Zest and halve the @lemon{1/2}. Roughly chop the @coriander{1} (stalks and all). Pick the @mint{1} leaves from their stalks and roughly chop (discard the stalks).

Pop the @ground coriander{1/2%tsp} and @cumin seeds{1/2%tsp} into a #pestle and mortar{} and roughly crush. Alternatively transfer to a #freezer bag{} and bash with the bottom of a #saucepan{}. Pop the aubergine and pepper slices onto a lightly oiled #baking tray{}, drizzle with @olive oil{2%tbsp}, season with @salt{} and sprinkle on half of the ground spices. Use your hands to make sure everything is coated. Roast in a single layer until soft and golden, ~{20-25%minutes}, turn halfway through cooking.

Meanwhile, heat a splash of @olive oil{} in a saucepan over medium-high heat. Add the red onion and cook until browned and softened, ~{5%minutes}. Stir in half the garlic, cook for ~{30%seconds} then add the @water{240%ml} and @chicken stock powder{1} and bring to the boil. Stir in the @bulgur wheat{120%g}, lemon zest and @chermoula spice mix{1}. Bring back up to the boil, pop a #lid{} on the pan and remove from the heat. Leave to the side for ~{12-15%minutes} or until ready to serve.

While everything else cooks, heat a drizzle of @olive oil{} in a #frying pan{} over medium-high heat. Pop the @lamb loin{2} onto a #plate{}, drizzle with oil and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Sprinkle on the remaining spice mix and use your hands to coat the meat.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands after handling raw meat.

When the pan is hot, brown the lamb on all sides, ~{2-3%minutes} total, then transfer to a baking tray and roast on the middle shelf of your oven for ~{9-10%minutes}. Wash the pan - we will use it again.

Pop the frying pan back onto high heat (no oil). Add the courgette slices and cook for ~{3%minutes} on each side.

> TIP: Allow the courgettes to brown and char.

When cooked, allow to cool then cut into 1cm chunks. Pop into a #bowl{} and mix in the @olives{30}(halved), @balsamic vinegar{12%ml}, @honey{15%ml} and @olive oil{1%tbsp}, remaining garlic, mint and coriander. When the peppers are cooked, carefully chop into 1cm chunks and add to the salsa.

When ready, rest the lamb wrapped in #foil{} for ~{5%minutes}. Meanwhile, stir half the salsa through the bulgur and season to taste with salt, pepper and lemon juice. Spoon onto your plates. Arrange the aubergine slices alongside. Spoon the remaining salsa neatly on top of the aubergine (don't leave the dressing in the bowl!). Slice the lamb thinly and place on top of the bulgur wheat. Crumble the @feta cheese{50%g} over and enjoy!